y, Torridge|Woolfardisworthy]]\n|-\n|Collamore\n|[[File:CollamoreArms.png|70px]]\n|''Gules billet\u00e9e or, three crescents of the second''\n|[[Saunton]], [[Braunton]]\n|-\n|[[Sir John Colleton, 1st Baronet|Colleton]]\n|[[File:ColletonArms.svg|70px]]\n|''Or, three stag's heads couped proper''<ref>Wotton, Thomas, Baronetage of England, 1771, Volume 2, Arms of Colleton Baronets; given by Vivian as ''roebuck's heads'', frequently interchangeable</ref>\n|Exeter\n|-\n|Collins\n|[[File:CollinsArms.svg|70px]]\n|''Azure, three torches or enflamed proper'' \n|[[Ottery St Mary]]; [[Offwell]] \n|-\n|Colman\n|[[File:ColmanArms.png|70px]]\n|''Per fess argent and sable, a cross flory between four mullets all counterchanged''\n|Gornhay, [[Tiverton, Devon|Tiverton]]\n|-\n|Cooke\n|[[File:Cooke (OfThorne Devon) Arms.png|70px]]\n|''Ermine, on a bend cotised gules three cats-a-mountain passant guardant or''\n|[[Thorne, Ottery St Mary]]\n|-\n|Coplestone\n|[[File:CoplestonArms.png|70px]]\n|''Argent, a chevron engrailed gules between three leopard's faces azure''\n|[[Copplestone|Copplestone, Colebrooke]]; [[Warleigh, Tamerton Foliot]]; [[Eggesford]]\n|-\n|Coram\n|[[File:CoramArms.png|70px]]\n|''Argent, a cross sable between four eagles displayed gules''\n|[[Ottery St Mary]]\n|-\n|Cory\n|[[File:CoryArms.png|70px]]\n|''Argent, a saltire sable on a chief azure three cinquefoils or''\n|Cory, [[West Putford]]\n|-\n|Cottell\n|[[File:CottellArms.png|70px]]\n|''Or, a bend gules''\n|Yealmbridge, [[Yealmpton]]; [[Sampford Peverell]];<ref>Pole, p.475</ref> Cottles Barton, [[North Tawton]]\n|-\n|[[William Cotton (bishop)|Cotton]]\n|[[File:CottonArms (Ancient).png|70px]]\n|''Argent, a bend sable between three [[Roundel (heraldry)|pellets]]''\n|[[Bishop's Palace, Exeter]]; [[Shobrooke]]; [[Silverton, Devon|Silverton]]\n|-\n|[[Earl of Devon|Courtenay]]\n|[[File:Blason Courtenay.svg|70px]]\n|''Or, three [[roundel (heraldry)|torteaux]]''\n|[[Okehampton Castle]]; [[Tiverton Castle]]; [[Manor of Powderham|