ively of John Kelloway of Cornwall and John Wadham (d.1578) of Merifield, Ilton, Somerset and Edge, Branscombe. See File:JoanTregarthinMonument BranscombeChurch Devon.PNG</ref>\n|[[Stafford Barton|Stowford/Stafford]], [[Dolton, Devon|Dolton]]\n|-\n|Kelly\n|[[File:KellyArms.png|70px]]\n|''Argent, a chevron between three billets gules''\n|[[Kelly House, Devon|Kelly]]\n|-\n|[[George Kendall (theologian)|Kendall]]\n|[[File:KendallArms.png|70px]]\n|''Argent, a chevron between three dolphins naiant embowed sable''\n|[[Kingsbridge]]; [[Cofton]], nr. [[Dawlish]]\n|-\n|[[John Kirkham (1472-1529)|Kirkham]]\n|[[File:KirkhamArms.png|70px]]\n|''Argent, three lions rampant gules a bordure engrailed sable''\n|[[Blagdon, Paignton]]; Bidwell, [[Newton St Cyres]]<ref>Vivian, p.517</ref>\n|-\n|Knapman\n|[[File:KnapmanArms.png|70px]]\n|''Or, on a cross gules between four Cornish choughs proper five blocks of tin marked with the letter W''\n|Wonson,<ref>Residence at Wonson per Baring-Gould, Sabine, ''An English Home'', p.277, ''Scapegraces''</ref> [[Throwleigh]]\n|}\n\n===L===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Name !! Escutcheon !! Blazon !! Seat, parish\n|-\n|Land\n|[[File:LandArms.png|70px]]\n|''Gyronny of eight or and sable a bend gules''\n|[[Silverton, Devon|Silverton]]\n|-\n|Langford\n|[[File:Langford OfBrattonClovelly Arms.png|70px]]\n|''Paly of six argent and gules, on a chief of the first a lion passant sable''\n|[[Bratton Clovelly]]\n|-\n|Lante<ref>John Lante (d.1614) was [[Mayor of Exeter]] and has a monument in Exeter Cathedral (Vivian, p.523)</ref>\n|[[File:LanteArms.png|70px]]\n|''Per pale argent and gules, a cross engrailed counterchanged''\n|[[Exeter]]\n|-\n|Larder\n|[[File:LarderArms.png|70px]]\n|''Argent, three piles sable each charged with as many bezants''\n|[[Upton Pyne]]\n|-\n|Leach\n|[[File:LeachArms.png|70px]]\n|''Ermine, on a chief engrailed gules three ducal coronets or''\n|[[Cadeleigh]]; All Hallows, Goldsmith Street, Exeter\n|-\n|Lee<ref>Richard Lee (d.1620) of T