allops argent a Cornish [[chough]] proper between two cinquefoils azure''\n|Bowhay, [[Dunchideock]]; Tor Newton, [[Torbryan|Tor Bryan]], (and [[Ingatestone Hall]], Essex).\n|-\n|Phillips\n|[[File:Phillips (of Alverdiscott) Arms.png|70px]]\n|''Or, on a chevron engrailed sable three eagle's heads erased argent''\n|[[Alverdiscott]]\n|-\n|Pincombe\n|[[File:PincombeArms.png|70px]]\n|''Per pale gules and azure, three close helmets argent garnished or''\n|[[South Molton]]; [[North Molton]]; [[Filleigh]]; [[East Buckland]]\n|-\n|Plumleigh<ref>Several members of the Plumleigh family served as [[Mayor of Dartmouth, Devon|Mayor of Dartmouth]]</ref>\n|[[File:PlumleighArms.png|70px]]\n|''(Argent?), a bend fusily gules''\n|[[Dartmouth, Devon|Dartmouth]]\n|-\n|Pointington\n|[[File:PointingtonArms.png|70px]]\n|''Argent, a bend gules between six fleurs-de-lys vert''\n|Penicott, [[Shobrooke]]\n|-\n|[[William Pole (antiquary)|Pole]]\n|[[File:PoleOfShuteArms.png|70px]]\n|''Azure sem\u00e9e of fleurs de lis or, a lion rampant argent''\n|[[Old Shute House|Shute]]; [[Colcombe Castle]]\n|-\n|[[Lewis Pollard|Pollard]]\n|[[File:PollardEscallopArms.PNG|70px]]\n|''Argent, a chevron sable between three escallops gules''\n|[[Way, St Giles in the Wood|Way]], [[St Giles in the Wood]]; [[Grilstone, Bishop's Nympton]]; [[King's Nympton]]; [[Langley, Yarnscombe]];  [[Abbots Bickington]]; [[Horwood, Devon|Horwood]]\n|-\n|[[Lewis Pollard|Pollard]] (''[[Way, St Giles in the Wood|de Way]]'' arms)<ref>de Via arms, as also used by the [[Davie Baronets|Davie family]] of [[Creedy, Sandford]], who claimed common origin with the Pollards from the ''de Way'' family, were quartered by Pollard with their escallop arms, (Prince, pp.284 (footnote), 783) but were sometimes used alone, as evidenced most notably by all the surviving Pollard monuments and ledger stones in Horwood Church</ref>\n|[[File:Davie OfCreedyDevon Arms Pierced.png|70px]]\n|''Argent, a chevron sable between three mullets pierced gules''\n|[[Way, 