ton): ''Or crusily fitchy, a lion rampant gules''\n*Bracy: Gules, a fess argent two mullets or in chief''\n*Braggo of Brags Marsh: ''Sable, a fess argent between three dolphins naiant or''\n*[[William Bradbridge|Bradbridge]], [[Bishop of Exeter]]: ''Azure, a pheon argent''\n*[[Thomas de Brantingham|Brantingham]], [[Bishop of Exeter]]: ''Sable, a fess embattled between three Catherine Wheels or''\n*Brereton of Exeter: ''..., two bars a crescent within a crescent''\n*Brent: ''Gules, a dragon wivern displayed argent''\n*Bryan of Tor Bryan: ''Or, three piles in point azure''\n*Britricheston of Britricheston: ''Argent, three boar's heads gules''\n*Broughton of Landkey: ''Argent, a chevron between three mullets gules''\n*Broughton of Hemioke: ''Argent, two bars and on a quarter (canton) gules a cross of the field''\n*Broughton: ''Sable, a chevron or between three stag's faces argent''\n*[[Walter Branscombe|Brounscombe]] (Branscombe), [[Bishop of Exeter]]: ''Or, on a chevron sable three quatrefoils or two keys in chief argent a sword in base argent''\n*Brewer of Tingbruer (Teign Brewer, now Teign Grace<ref>Pole, p.261; Pevsner, p.793</ref>)  : ''Argent, four (bars) gemelles azure over all a chevron engrailed gules''\n*Brewer (Briwer/Brigwer) of Tor Brewer (Tor Mohun,<ref>Pole, p.272</ref> now Torquay)  : ''Gules, two bends und\u00e9e or''\n*[[Brutus Browne|Browne]] of  (Brown\u2019s Ilash<ref>Risdon, p.271</ref>/Brownishilarshe<ref>Vivian, p.112</ref> Brownlarsh<ref>Westcote, Thomas, View of Devonshire</ref> now East Brown\u2019s, site of old mansion, by Hillash Moor, surrounded by ancient deerpark<ref>Old Map of , Langtree, Devon Detailed Old Victorian Ordnance Survey 6 inch to 1 mile Old Map (1888-1913) [http://www.archiuk.com/cgi-bin/build_nls_historic_map.pl?search_location=,%20Langtree,%20Devon&latitude=50.913594&longitude=-4.206259&password=freesearch@freesearch.com]</ref> built by Sir Thomas Browne<ref>Risdon, p.272</ref> (d.1613), elder brother of [[Brutus Browne]]