owns'', about 1 mile S-W of Langtree village</ref> [[Langtree]]\n|-\n|Bruton\n|[[File:BrutonArms.png|70px]]\n|''Per pale gules and azure, a fess between two chevrons argent''\n|[[Heavitree]]\n|-\n|Budockshed\n|[[File:BudockshedArms.png|70px]]\n|''Sable, three fusils in fess between three buck's faces argent''\n|[[Budockshed]], [[St Budeaux]]\n|-\n|Burgoyne\n|[[File:BurgoyneArms.svg|70px]]\n|''Azure, a hound passant argent''\n|[[South Tawton]]\n|-\n|Burnard<ref>Charles Frederick Burnard (1816-post 1894) of Chatsworth Lodge in the parish of Compton Gifford, near Plymouth, Devon, was Mayor of Plymouth in 1882 (Vivian, p.849)</ref>\n|[[File:BurnardArms.svg|70px]]\n|''Argent, three escallops in bend between two bendlets azure in chief and in base a leopard's face jessant-de-lys of the last''\n|Chatsworth Lodge, [[Compton Gifford]]\n|-\n|Burnby\n|[[File:BurnbyArms.png|70px]]\n|''Argent, two bars counter-embattled ermines''\n|Burnby, [[Bratton Clovelly]]\n|-\n|Burrington\n|[[File:BurringtonArms.svg|70px]]\n|''Argent, a lion rampant sable flory or''\n|Idford, [[Chudleigh]]; [[Sandford, Devon|Sandford]]\n|-\n|Bury\n|[[File:BuryOfColletonDevonArms.PNG|70px]]\n|''Ermine, on a bend engrailed azure three fleurs-de-lys or''\n|[[Colleton, Chulmleigh]]\n|-\n|Butler<ref>Although [[Thomas Butler, 7th Earl of Ormonde]] (d.1515) (whose wife was Anne Hankford the heiress of [[Annery, Monkleigh]], Devon, and whose heraldry survives on a bench-end in Monkleigh Church) is known to have died without male progeny (the earldom descended to his distant male cousin), the family of Butler of Parkham submitted a pedigree to the heralds at the Heraldic Visitation of Devon of 1620 which claimed descent from a certain ''Humfridus Boteler de Annery'' (Vivian, p.104), whose identity is therefore uncertain. The arms however of Butler of Parkham are the arms of Butler, Earl of Ormond (''Gules, three covered cups or'') [[Difference (heraldry)|differenced]] with a field ''azure''.</ref>\n|[[File:Butler (OfParkham Devon) Arms.png|70px]]\n|''Azure, three covered cups or''\n|[[Parkham]]; [[Littleham]]\n|}\n\n===C===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Name !! Escutcheon !! Blazon !! Seat, parish\n|-\n|[[Richard Cabell|Cabell]]\n|[[File:CabellArms.png|70px]]\n|''Vert fretty argent, over all a fess gules''\n|Brook, [[Buckfastleigh]]\n|-\n|Cade\n|[[File:CadeArms.png|70px]]\n|''Argent, three piles in point wavy sable''\n|[[Fremington, Devon|Fremington]]; [[Barnstaple]]\n|-\n|Callard\n|[[File:CallardArms.png|70px]]\n|''Gyronny of six or and sable, three Moor's heads sidefaced couped proper wreathed round the temples (argent)''<ref>Wreath, per Pole, p.475: ''argent'', per Vivian, p.127, ''of the first and second'', i.e. ''or and sable''</ref>\n|Callard, [[Burrington, Devon|Burrington]] (?);<ref>Location of Callard uncertain, however an ancient farmhouse of than name survives in the parish of Burrington (see listed building text [http://www.britishlistedbuildings.co.uk/en-97136-callard-farmhouse-burrington-devon#.WFfq-H25Qqd])</ref> Southcott, [[Winkleigh]]\n|-\n|Calmady\n|[[File:CalmadyArms.PNG|70px]]\n|''Azure, a chevron between three pears or''\n|Calmady, Penfound, [[Poundstock]], Cornwall;[[Langdon Court, Devon|Langdon]], [[Wembury]]; Stoke Climsland, Cornwall; Leawood, [[Bridestowe]];\n|-\n|[[John Calwoodleigh|Calwoodleigh]]\n|[[File:CalwoodleighArms.png|70px]]\n|''Azure, two wings conjoined argent over all on a fess gules three [[bezant]]s''\n|[[Calwoodleigh]] (mod:[[Calverleigh]]); Cove, [[Stoodleigh]]; [[Uplowman]]\n|-\n|Carew\n|[[File:CarewArms.png|70px]]\n|''Or, three lions passant sable''\n|Crowcombe; [[Antony, Cornwall]]; [[Tiverton Castle]]; [[Haccombe]]; [[Bickleigh Castle]]; [[Mohuns Ottery]]\n|-\n|Carswell\n|[[File:CarswellArms.png|70px]]\n|''Sable, a bend or''\n| Carswell, [[Holbeton]]\n|-\n|Carwythan\n|[[File:CarwythanArms.png|70px]]\n|''Argent, a fleur-de-lys gules a bordure engrailed of the second''\n|Panston, [[Sydenham Damerel]]; St Petrock, Exeter; Manaton; 