von|Hartland]]\n|-\n|[[Chudleigh baronets|Chudleigh]]\n|[[File:ChudleighArms.PNG|70px]]\n|''Ermine, three lions rampant gules''\n|[[Manor of Ashton|Ashton]]; [[Haldon House|Haldon]]\n|-\n|Clapham<ref>The inscribed mural monument of Raleigh Clapham (1587-1636), Apothecary, survives in St Peter's Church, Barnstaple. Image see [https://www.flickr.com/photos/52219527@N00/19502499491]</ref>\n|[[File:Clapham (OfBarnstaple Devon) Arms.png|70px]]\n|''Argent, on a bend azure six fleurs-de-lys or, two, two and two''\n|[[Barnstaple]]; ([[Beamsley]] Hall,<ref>The home from 1980-2005 of the son and heir of the 11th Duke of Devonshire, and today part of the Bolton Hall estate of the Duke of Devonshire</ref> Yorkshire)\n|-\n|Clement<ref>John Clement was a member of the Corporation of Plymouth in 1620 and married Judith Sparke, a sister of [[John Sparke (died 1640)|John Sparke]] (c. 1574\u20131640), MP, of The Friary, in the parish of St Jude, Plymouth, Devon (Vivian, pp.193, 856)</ref>\n|[[File:ClementArms.png|70px]]\n|''Argent, two bends wavy gules on a chief of the last three estoiles or''\n|[[Plymouth]]\n|-\n|[[Baron Clifford of Chudleigh|Clifford]]\n|[[File:Arms of Clifford.svg|70px]]\n|''Chequy or and azure a fess gules''\n|[[Chudleigh]]; [[Kingsteignton]].\n|-\n|Clobbery\n|[[File:ClobberyArms.png|70px]]\n|''Argent, a chevron between three bats displayed sable''\n|[[Bradstone]]\n|-\n|[[John Clotworthy, 1st Viscount Massereene|Clotworthy]]\n|[[File:ClotworthyArmsInkscape.png|70px]]\n|''Azure, a chevron ermine between three chaplets or''\n|Clotworthy, [[Wembworthy]]; [[Rashleigh, Wembworthy]]\n|-\n|Cockeram\n|[[File:CockeramArms.png|70px]]\n|''Argent, on a bend sable three leopard's faces of the field'' \n|[[Hillersdon House|Hillersdon]], [[Cullompton]]; Growen, [[Cullompton]]\n|-\n|Cockshead\n|[[File:CocksheadArms.png|70px]]\n|''Azure, a cinquefoil argent a chief lozengy of the second and gules''\n|[[Chulmleigh]]\n|-\n|[[Richard Coffin (1456-1523)|Coffin]]\n|[[File:CoffinOfMonkleighArms.PNG|70px]]\n|''Azure, three bezants between eight crosses crosslet or''\n|[[Portledge Manor|Portledge]], [[Alwington]]; [[Monkleigh]]; [[Inwardleigh]]\n|-\n|[[Feudal barony of Bampton|Cogan]]\n|[[File:CoganArms.PNG|70px]]\n|''Gules, three (mulbery) leaves argent''<ref>As blazoned by [[William Pole (antiquary)|Sir William Pole]] (d.1635), Collections Towards a Description of the County of Devon, Sir John-William de la Pole (ed.), London, 1791, p.447 and as depicted [[Quartering (heraldry)|quartered]] on monument of Lady Frances Bourchier (1587-1612), daughter of [[William Bourchier, 3rd Earl of Bath]] (d.1623), in the Bedford Chapel at [[Chenies]], Buckinghamshire.[http://www.middlesex-heraldry.org.uk/publications/monographs/chenies/cheniesBKM-monuments.htm] The arms of Cogan (a branch of which later became known as [[Goggin]]) are variously blazoned elsewhere as oak leaves, aspen leaves, etc.</ref>\n|[[Bampton, Devon|Bampton]]\n|-\n|[[John Cole (born c.1376)|Cole]]\n|[[File:ColeArms.png|70px]]\n|''Argent, a bull passant sable armed or a bordure of the second bezant\u00e9e''\n|[[Nethway, Brixham]]; [[Slade, Cornwood|Slade]], [[Cornwood]]; [[Bucks Mills|Bucks]], [[Woolfardisworthy, Torridge|Woolfardisworthy]]\n|-\n|Collamore\n|[[File:CollamoreArms.png|70px]]\n|''Gules billet\u00e9e or, three crescents of the second''\n|[[Saunton]], [[Braunton]]\n|-\n|[[Sir John Colleton, 1st Baronet|Colleton]]\n|[[File:ColletonArms.svg|70px]]\n|''Or, three stag's heads couped proper''<ref>Wotton, Thomas, Baronetage of England, 1771, Volume 2, Arms of Colleton Baronets; given by Vivian as ''roebuck's heads'', frequently interchangeable</ref>\n|Exeter\n|-\n|Collins\n|[[File:CollinsArms.svg|70px]]\n|''Azure, three torches or enflamed proper'' \n|[[Ottery St Mary]]; [[Offwell]] \n|-\n|Colman\n|[[File:ColmanArms.png|70px]]\n|''Per fess argent and sable, a cross flory between four mullets all counterchanged''\n|Gornhay, [[Tiverton, Devon|Tiverton]]\n|-\n|Cooke\n|[[File:Cooke (OfThorne Devon) Arms.png|70px]]\n|''Ermine, on a bend cotised gules three cats-a-mountain passant guardant or''\n|[[Thorne, Ottery St Mary]]\n|-\n|Coplestone\n|[[File:CoplestonArms.png|70px]]\n|''Argent, a chevron engrailed gules between three leopard's faces azure''\n|[[Copplestone|Copplestone, Colebrooke]]; [[Warleigh, Tamerton Foliot]]; [[Eggesford]]\n|-\n|Coram\n|[[File:CoramArms.png|70px]]\n|''Argent, a cross sable between four eagles displayed gules''\n|[[Ottery St Mary]]\n|-\n|Cory\n|[[File:CoryArms.png|70px]]\n|''Argent, a saltire sable on a chief azure three cinquefoils or''\n|Cory, [[West Putford]]\n|-\n|Cottell\n|[[File:CottellArms.png|70px]]\n|''Or, a bend gules''\n|Yealmbridge, [[Yealmpton]]; [[Sampford Peverell]];<ref>Pole, p.475</ref> Cottles Barton, [[North Tawton]]\n|-\n|[[William Cotton (bishop)|Cotton]]\n|[[File:CottonArms (Ancient).png|70px]]\n|''Argent, a bend sable between three [[Roundel (heraldry)|pellets]]''\n|[[Bishop's Palace, Exeter]]; [[Shobrooke]]; [[Silverton, Devon|Silverton]]\n|-\n|[[Earl of Devon|Courtenay]]\n|[[File:Blason Courtenay.svg|70px]]\n|''Or, three [[roundel (heraldry)|torteaux]]''\n|[[Okehampton Castle]]; [[Tiverton Castle]]; [[Manor of Powderham|Powderham]]; [[Manor of Molland|Molland]]; [[Colcombe Castle|Colcombe]], [[Colyton, Devon|Colyton]]; [[Upcott, Cheriton Fitzpaine]]; [[Moretonhampstead|Moreton Hampstead]]<ref>Pole, p.263</ref>\n|-\n|Croker\n|[[File:CrokerArms.png|70px]]\n|''Argent, a chevron engrailed gules between three crows proper''\n|[[Croker's Hele, Meeth]]; [[Lyneham, Yealmpton]]\n|-\n|[[Francis Crossing|Crossing]]\n|[[File:CrossingArms.PNG|70px]]\n|''Or, on a chevron azure between three [[Cross|crosses crosslet fitch\u00e9e]] gules as many [[bezant]]s''\n|Exeter\n|-\n|Cruwys\n|[[File:CruwysArms.png|70px]]\n|''Azure, a bend per bend indented argent and gules between six escallops or''\n|[[Cruwys Morchard]]\n|-\n|Crymes / Grymes\n|[[File:CrymesArms.png|70px]]\n|''Or, three bars gules each charged with as many 