d]]\n|-\n|Downe\n|[[File:DowneArms.png|70px]]\n|''Gules, a buck's head cabossed ermine attired or''\n|Tushill,<ref>Reed, Margaret A., Pilton, its Past and its People, Barnstaple, 1985, p.243</ref> [[Pilton, Devon|Pilton]]\n|-\n|Dowrish\n|[[File:DowrishArms.png|70px]]\n|''Argent, a bend cotised sable a bordure engrailed of the last''\n|[[Dowrish]], [[Sandford, Devon|Sandford]]\n|-\n|[[Bernard Drake|Drake]]\n|[[File:Drake (ofAsh) Arms.png|70px]]\n|''Argent, a wyvern wings displayed and tail nowed gules''\n|[[Ash, Musbury]]; Mount Drake, [[Musbury]]\n|-\n|[[Francis Drake|Drake]]\n|[[File:DrakeArms.PNG|70px]]\n|''Sable, a fess wavy between two estoiles argent''\n|[[Buckland Abbey]], [[Buckland Monachorum]]; [[Nutwell]],  [[Woodbury, Devon|Woodbury]]\n|-\n|[[Edward Drew|Drewe]]\n|[[File:DreweArms.PNG|70px]]\n|''Ermine, a lion passant gules''\n|[[Sharpham, Ashprington]]; [[Killerton]], [[Broadclyst]]; [[The Grange, Broadhembury]]\n|-\n|[[Nicholas Duck|Duck]]\n|[[File:Duck arms.PNG|70px]]\n|''Or, on a fess wavy sable three lozenges of the field''\n|[[Heavitree]], Exeter; [[Mount Radford, Exeter]]\n|-\n|[[Richard Duke (English lawyer)|Duke]]\n|[[File:Duke (Of Otterton,Devon) Arms.png|70px]]\n|''Per fesse argent and azure, three chaplets counterchanged''\n|[[Otterton]]\n|-\n|Dyer<ref>Richard Dyer c.1545/54 purchased Yarde from the Yarde family, whose longtime seat it had been, following their removal to Bradley (Risdon, p.176; Allan et al., p.244). His great-great-great-grandson was the botanist Richard Dyer (born 1651), a Fellow of [[Oriel College, Oxford]], who inherited Yarde from his elder brother William Dyer (d.1714) and rebuilt it in 1718 (John Allan, Nat Alcock, David Dawson, ''West Country Households, 1500-1700'', p.244 ''The Stained Hangings at Yarde Farm''[https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=0kToCQAAQBAJ&pg=PA244&lpg=PA244&dq=dyer+malborough+devon&source=bl&ots=dZp0q7SySa&sig=TjZy1_T92YPQVLYCU5SJEkMeUh0&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwiEzOWCs8rRAhWmI8AKHVnnCskQ6AEIOTAG#v=onepage&q=dyer%20malborough%20devon&f=false])</ref>\n|[[File:DyerArms.png|70px]]\n|''Or, a chief indented gules a mullet for difference''\n|Yarde, [[Malborough]]\n|-\n|[[Baron Dynham|Dynham]]\n|[[File:Dynham OfWortham Devon Arms.png|70px]]\n|''Gules, four fusils in fess a bordure ermine''\n|[[Wortham, Lifton]]\n|}\n\n===E===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Name !! Escutcheon !! Blazon !! Seat, parish\n|-\n|[[Earl of Mount Edgcumbe|Edgcumbe]]\n|[[File:EdgcumbeArms.png|70px]]\n|''Gules, on a bend ermines cotised or three boar's heads couped argent''\n|Edgcumbe, [[Milton Abbot]]; [[Tavistock]]; Ottery, [[Lamerton]] ([[Mount Edgcumbe House|Mount Edgcumbe]], Cornwall; [[Cotehele]], Cornwall)\n|-\n|[[Thomas Edmondes|Edmonds]]\n|[[File:EdmondsArms.png|70px]]\n|''Or, a chevron azure on a canton of the second a boar's head couped between three fleurs-de-lys of the first''\n|[[Plymouth]]\n|-\n|Edwards\n|[[File:Edwards (OfExeter) Arms.png|70px]]\n|''Per bend sinister ermine and ermines, a lion rampant or''\n|[[Church of St Mary Major, Exeter|St Mary Major]], Exeter\n|-\n|Elford\n|[[File:ElfordArms.png|70px]]\n|''Per pale argent and azure, a lion rampant gules''\n|[[Sheepstor]], [[Yelverton, Devon|Yelverton]]\n|-\n|Eliot\n|[[File:Eliot OfTavistock Arms.png|70px]]\n|''Azure, a fess or''\n|[[Tavistock]]\n|-\n|Ellacott\n|[[File:EllacottArms.png|70px]]\n|''Lozengy or and azure, a bordure gules''\n|Milbury;<ref>Location of Milbury unknown. Several streets in [[Exminster]] are named \"Milbury\"</ref> [[Exeter]], [[St Petrock's Church, Exeter|St Petrock's]]\n|-\n|[[Earl of St Germans|Ellyot]]\n|[[File:EliotArms.png|70px]]\n|''Argent, a fess gules between two bars gemelles wavy azure''\n|[[Farringdon, Devon|Farringdon]]\n|-\n|English\n|[[File:ProuseArms.PNG|70px]]\n|''Sable, three lioncels rampant argent''\n|[[Stockleigh English]]\n|-\n|[[Nicholas Eveleigh (died 1618)|Eveleigh]]\n|[[File:EveleighArms.png|70px]]\n|''Per pale or and sable, two chevronels between three griffins passant count